# Some observations:
# Client is more likely to subscribe if they are more educated
# Client is more likely to subscribe if they are default is no
# Client is more likely to subscribe if they are a student or retired
# Client is more likely to subscribe on the first day of the month
# Client is more likely to subscribe on in sept, oct, dec and in march (but there are also the least number of records for these months)
# Client is more likely to subscribe if poutcome is success

# Contact does not add anything to our evaluation so we can drop it

In [34]:
## function to get confusion matrix in a proper format
def draw_cm( actual, predicted ):
    cm = confusion_matrix( actual, predicted)
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True,  fmt='.2f', xticklabels = [0,1] , yticklabels = [0,1] )
    plt.ylabel('Observed')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted')
    plt.show()

The Marketing team wants to maximize the prediction of the number of customers taht will subscribe to term deposit,so they want to minimize the number of False Negatives. Therefore a high recall number is important.

Looking at the different algorithms, Gradient Boost classifier is the best choice as that gives a good Recall value while maintaining a better fit. There are some algorithms (Decision Tree, Bagging Classifier, RandomForest) which have a slightly better recall but they suffer from overfitting
